race.comment: FINE WINE (8) was ridden hard to lead then tired late and missed the placings on debut over 900m at Newcastle last start. Will learn a lot from that experience. Has to contend with a wide gate but with even luck is sure to be in the finish. Recent Rosehill trial winner ASK DI (7) demands respect on debut for the Ryan/Alexiou camp. By Snitzel from a Bernardini mare. Draws the fence and is sure to attract interest, particularly coming out of the inside gate. TAXATION (10) is a Joe Pride first starter by I Am Invincible from a Lonhro mare. Won a Warwick Farm trial in mid-September which is the basis for her tight position in early markets. Plenty of trial experience so should be up for this. Zoustar debutante CALL ME SASSY (3) has been to the trials four times and been prominent on each occasion. Well-schooled to make a decisive introduction to racing. COMPOSED (4) is trialling well for Peter Snowden and is ready to make an impact on debut.
